LISBON, July 22 (Reuters) - Following are some of the main stories in Portuguese newspapers on Tuesday. Reuters has not verified these stories and does not vouch for their accuracy.

* Apollo and Permira funds competing for Tranquilidade insurance firm, but creditor protection regime at Espirito Santo International may delay sale (Diario Economico) * Banco Espirito Santo <BES.LS> to define measures to boost financial strength in September (Negocios) * Banco Espirito Santo seeks to calm down clients, will be advised by foreign bank (Jornal de Noticias)